$interpreted: Slums Elder: Have you heard about Phil? He's...
Slums Woman: I know. He just disappeared like that, so creepy...
Slums Man: He's a really good child. I hope they find him soon.
Hyacinthus: Hey, where are you guys going?
Leah: You scared me...we're on our way to work, at the dye workshop.
Lio: Cin, everyone's talking about Phil. Did something happen to him?
Hyacinthus: Phil went missing for no apparent reason. Nobody knows what's going on.
Lio: Did he...get eaten by the Ragdoll Coroner?
Slums Elder: The Ragdoll Coroner? You mean that scary legend?
Slums Woman: Someone saw Phil leaving the Slums at night. Maybe he really...
Nigel: You guys, if you have time to blabber about horror stories, I suggest you put that time to good use and help us find him!
Slums Man: B-But...we've searched the nearby areas thoroughly, and yet we still can't find him.
Slums Woman: If the legend is true, then three days later, Phil's body will appear at Garbage Mountain...
Hyacinthus: Shut up! Don't say that!
Eugene: How long are you guys going to slack off! It's just a little brat who's gone missing. Don't think you get to mope around!
Hyacinthus: Damn bastard...Okay, okay, we got it!
Lio: Hey, let's go back. It's so dark out here and it's super scary!
Leah: Coward! Our good friend is missing. Do you not care about him?
Lio: I want to know where Phil went too...
Leah: Then stop whining and help me find him!
Leah: Lio, I'm going open this. Help me!
Lio: Huh? You...you sure about this!?
Lio: H-Help!
Lio: Ouch!
Leah: Lio!
Lio: D-Don't come near me!
Nigel: Running outside at this time of the night, are you trying to get yourself killed!?
Leah: We just wanted to help find Phil...
Nigel: None of your business. You damn near cost your brother his life with your recklessness!
Leah: So we're going to rely on just you? Phil's been missing for days already; you've found nothing!
Lio: Stop arguing...
Nigel: Whatever, go back to the Slums and stay there! I don't want to waste my stamina protecting useless people!
Leah: Y-You're the useless one! Every night, you abandon the Slums and disappear to nowhere!
Lio: Leah, stop this. Cin told us. Nigel leaves every night for work. He's doing it for the livelihood of the Slums.
Leah: How dare you not speak up for me!? I am your older sister!
Leah: UGH, I'm so mad! Idiots, all of you are freakin' idiots!!
